</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="709" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="18.[130,1340,2403,3261]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[130,368,2991,3024]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Peterson’s Long-fingered Bat is nocturnal. It uses caves as daytime roosts. Echolocation calls have downward FM signals, with maximum frequencies of 95-115 kHz, minimum frequencies of 48-50 kHz, peak frequencies of 52-53-9 kHz, durations of 2:5-3-3 milliseconds, and intervals of 63-8-76-7 milliseconds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
